node.text:
It’s kind of a long story….

So years ago, in 2017 in my amateur bourbon hunting days, I walk into a shop in Soho (London) called @gerryswinesspirits7246 

They’re super cool and let me browse the aisle of bourbon behind the partition. I find an OWA 107 and while I’m buying it, they pull out a @smoothambler Old Scout Cask Strength, Single Barrel 10 year store pick, saying I should buy that too.  But I was a novice at the time and never heard of Smooth Ambler, so I refused.

That was a decision I ended up regretting. And I vowed to never turn down a bourbon pick of theirs again.

Fast forward a bit to 2018 and I’m back in London. I head over to Gerry’s to see what they have. They tell me that they have an @eaglerarebourbon pick coming soon. I can’t wait. 

Later that year I’m back in London and I head back to the store. Still no Eagle pick in!

Finally at the end of 2018 or maybe beginning of 2019 I get word it’s come in, but I’m not in London! So I buy a couple bottles on their website and have my buddy in London swoop in to pick it up - one for me and one for him.

2019 comes and goes and I haven’t had the chance to get to London to pick the bottle up.  And then came 2020 which was a blur.

So we find ourselves in August 2021, and my buddy hops across the pond, and brings this with him! 

Finally some closure to a story that began 4 years ago!  Good things come to those who wait!
.
.
.
